cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper presents a framework for few-shot learning using deep learning techniques, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The framework involves comparing images and computing relation scores, which suggests the involvement of computer vision (cs.CV) techniques. The paper also mentions the use of meta-learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the framework can be extended to zero-shot learning, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques. Finally, the use of deep learning techniques suggests the involvement of neural networks (cs.NE).
